{"itemid":2074,"subject":"More Cool Wild Cards Stuff","event":"A couple of cool new pieces about Wild Cards this morning.\r\n\r\nThe second installment of Katy Rask's Wild Cards reread is up today on Tor.com.\r\n\r\n http://www.tor.com/2017/04/05/killer-space-yeast-attacks-wild-cards-ii-is-a-superpowered-love-letter-to-science-fiction/\r\n\r\nThis one is about volume two, ACES HIGH. \r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/452374/452374_300.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"><img src=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/453060/453060_300.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"><img src=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/453331/453331_300.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"> \r\n\r\nGo and join the fun and let your voice be heard.  Authors have been known to drop by from time to time.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, over on the official Wild Cards website, we've added a new blog post by Mary Anne Mohanraj about the creation of her popular character, Natya the dancer.\r\n\r\n http://www.wildcardsworld.com/the-origins-of-natya/\r\n\r\n Oh, and I should also mention that Walter Jon's tribute to Roger Zelazny and Croyd Crenson, originally published on the WC website, is now available on Tor.com as well:\r\n\r\n http://www.tor.com/2017/03/31/the-best-wild-cards-character-that-i-didnt-create-roger-zelaznys-the-sleeper/#comment-658746\r\n\r\nHappy reading, aces.","ditemid":531050,"eventtime":"2017-04-05 15:46:00","props":{"current_mood":"bouncy","current_location":"Santa Fe","taglist":"internet, tor, wild cards, #comment","crosspost_tw_log":"[Wed Apr  5 21:46:24 2017]R [Wed Apr  5 21:46:25 2017]https://twitter.com/GRRMspeaking/status/849740030885154817 ","current_moodid":59,"commentalter":1492274223,"crosspost_tw":"https://twitter.com/GRRMspeaking/status/849740030885154817","ratingbot_comment":"[cyr:-|ua:-|noncyr:13|by:-|ru:-|rureg:-]","revnum":2,"personifi_tags":"nterms:no","interface":"web","hasscreened":1,"homepage_reposted":63986505,"opt_lockcomments":1,"picture_keyword":"wc